JOHANNESBURG - Police in the Eastern Cape have arrested two suspects on stock theft charges after finding six sheep crammed inside a Toyota Tazz. In a Tweet on Sunday, the South African Police Service confirmed the incident, which took place in Cathcart - a small town between Stutterheim and Queenstown. READ: ANC condemns stock theft case involving MP released on a warning The suspects will appear in court on Monday.  (Photo: Saps) eNCA